aa(lp107
VThe first issue:
p108
aVImagine a potential enemy announcing
p109
aVthey're building a cyberwar unit,
p110
aVbut only for their country's defense.
p111
aVOkay, but what distinguishes it
p112
aVfrom an offensive unit?
p113
aVIt gets even more complicated
p114
aVwhen the doctrines of use become ambiguous.
p115
aVJust 3 years ago, both the U.S. and France
p116
aVwere saying they were investing militarily in cyberspace,
p117
aVstrictly to defend their IT systems.
p118
aVBut today both countries say
p119
aVthe best defense is to attack.
p120
aVAnd so, they're joining China,
p121
aVwhose doctrine of use for 15 years has been
p122
aVboth defensive and offensive.
